<!--*********************************************
            Hint
**********************************************-->
<hint name="helpSection"><title>Worked Example</title>
<p>Here is a similar worked example:</p>

<example>
<p><em>If <m>a_1 = 6</m> and <m>a_n = $expr</m>, find <m>a_5</m>.</em></p>
<p>In this example, we create a table since the requested <m>n</m> value is sufficiently small that a step-wise or recursive solution is not overly laborious. Here is a similar worked example:</p>

  <p><em><alert>Solution.</alert></em></p>
  <md>
    <mrow>a_1 \amp= 6\;\;\;\amp\text{given information}</mrow>
    <mrow>a_2 \amp= 2\cdot 6 - 1 = 11\;\;\;\amp\text{substitute}\;\; a_{n-1} = a_1 = 6</mrow>
    <mrow>a_3 \amp= 2\cdot 11 - 1 = 21\;\;\;\amp\text{substitute}\;\;  a_{n-1} = a_2 = 11</mrow>
    <mrow>a_4 \amp= 2\cdot 21 - 1 = 41\;\;\;\amp\text{substitute}\;\;  a_{n-1} = a_3 = 21</mrow>
    <mrow>a_5 \amp= 2\cdot 41 - 1 = 81\;\;\;\amp\text{substitute}\;\;  a_{n-1} = a_4 = 41</mrow>
  </md>
</example>  

  </hint>

<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
<p>To solve for <m>a_$p</m> with the given recursive formula, we construct a table of values:</p>
<conditionalContent>
  <case condition="$p = 4">
    <md>
      <mrow>a_1 \amp= $a</mrow>
      <mrow>a_2 \amp= $step1 = $step1{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_3 \amp= $step2 = $step2{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_4 \amp= $step3 = $step3{simplify}</mrow>
    </md>
  </case>
  <case condition="$p = 5">
    <md>
      <mrow>a_1 \amp= $a</mrow>
      <mrow>a_2 \amp= $step1 = $step1{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_3 \amp= $step2 = $step2{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_4 \amp= $step3 = $step3{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_5 \amp= $step4 = $step4{simplify}</mrow>
    </md>
  </case>
  <case condition="$p = 6">
    <md>
      <mrow>a_1 \amp= $a</mrow>
      <mrow>a_2 \amp= $step1 = $step1{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_3 \amp= $step2 = $step2{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_4 \amp= $step3 = $step3{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_5 \amp= $step4 = $step4{simplify}</mrow>
      <mrow>a_6 \amp= $step5 = $step5{simplify}</mrow>
    </md>
  </case>
</conditionalContent>
<p>If the student prefers to try to discover an explicit solution based on the pattern, one such equivalent explicit solution is: <me>a_n = (a_1 - 1)\cdot2^{(n - 1)} + 1</me>.</p>
</solution>
</problem>



